When an admin denies a user's resource access request, the resource list still showed "Apply for access" — because the `denied` status fell through to the default branch. This also caused a duplicate-key DB error when the user clicked it.

## Changes

- **`club-detail.html`** — Insert a `denied` branch in the resource access status chain, before the "Apply for access" button:
  ```html
  } @else if (getApprovalStatus(resource.id) === 'denied') {
    <span class="approval-badge denied">Denied</span>
  } @else if (userMembership()?.status === 'approved') {
    <!-- Apply for access button -->
  ```

- **`club-detail.scss`** — Add `.approval-badge.denied` styled with M3 error-container tokens, consistent with the existing `approved`/`pending` pill chips:
  ```scss
  &.denied {
    background-color: var(--mat-sys-error-container);
    color: var(--mat-sys-on-error-container);
  }
  ```
